instruction: Patient missed two active birth control pills during finals, doubled up on doses, and is experiencing spotting and heavy legs during sprints.

attributes.narrative: Patient missed two active birth control pills during finals, doubled up on doses, and is experiencing spotting and heavy legs during sprints.

instruction: From tonight, take one blue tablet at 9 p.m., no doses. Because you skipped more than 48 hours, add condoms for seven days. If any pill is over 24 hours late, swallow it immediately, continue the pack, and restart seven-day condom clock. Expected side effects include breast tenderness, mild water weight, mood flutter—settle by the second pack and don’t hurt VO₂ max. But calf pain or sudden chest tightness means ER, no apologies. Tie the pill to tooth-brushing, set two alarms, and keep a backup strip in your gear bag.
